arts.ttl: Orellano, Celentano help Cincinnati edge Real Salt Lake 1-0 to take lead in Eastern Conference
arts.sum: Luca Orellano scored late in the second half and Roman Celentano turned away seven shots as FC Cincinnati snapped Real Salt Lake’s five-match unbeaten run with a 1-0 victory on Saturday night, grabbing the lead in the Eastern Conference and Supporters’ Shield races with the win. Rafael Cabral finished with three saves for Real Salt Lake (8-11-4), which had four wins during its unbeaten run.
